cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper deals with transfer reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of universal successor representations (USR) and USR approximator (USRA) in this work suggests that it may fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve visual inputs, which could also place it under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with control and decision-making, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
